  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nSolidity 0.6.3 added a debug flag one can pass to the compiler, where the compiler builds in revert strings for any compiler-added reverts.  (See the [release notes](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/releases/tag/v0.6.3).)\r\n\r\nI don't think this is in our whitelist of options to pass along to the Solidity compiler; it should be whitelisted so users can put this in their truffle-config and compile their contracts with this debug option if they want.",
